1. Project Overview
This project demonstrates the complete DevOps lifecycle applied to a real-world MERN (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) stack Online Bookstore application. The project covers containerization using Docker, orchestration using Kubernetes (Minikube), and real-time monitoring using Prometheus and Grafana.
The application was originally deployed locally on a development machine. Through this project, it has been transformed into a production-grade, self-healing, auto-scaling, and fully monitored cloud-native application.

2. Problem Statement & Solution
2.1 Problem Statement
Traditional MERN stack applications face several challenges in production environments:
•	No fault tolerance — if the server crashes, the app goes down completely
•	No auto-scaling — cannot handle sudden traffic spikes
•	No visibility — no way to monitor CPU, memory, or pod health in real time
•	Manual deployment — every update requires manual intervention
•	No alerting — no notifications when something goes wrong
2.2 Solution
By applying DevOps tools — Docker, Kubernetes, Prometheus, and Grafana — we solved all the above problems:
•	Docker: Packages the app into portable containers that run anywhere
•	Kubernetes: Manages containers, provides self-healing and auto-scaling
•	Prometheus: Collects real-time metrics from all pods
•	Grafana: Visualizes metrics in beautiful dashboards
•	Alertmanager: Sends alerts when pods crash or resource usage spikes

